WEBVTT

00:13.146 --> 00:15.282
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:15.315 --> 00:17.351
HAM OR PEPPERONI?
HAM.
HAM.

00:17.384 --> 00:20.053
WHAT DO YOU WANT?
YOU WANT MONEY?
I WANT WEED.

00:20.087 --> 00:22.389
I HEAR YOU GET GREAT SHIT
FROM AFGHANISTAN.

00:22.422 --> 00:24.124
IS STEVIE AROUND?

00:24.157 --> 00:26.159
NANCE, YOU'RE GONNA BE GETTING
SOME PAPERS FROM MY LAWYER.

00:26.193 --> 00:28.896
JUST FOR SCHOOL ENROLLMENT,
TO ‐‐ TO MAKE IT LEGAL.

00:28.929 --> 00:32.299
MAKE WHAT LEGAL?
CUSTODY,
SO HE CAN REGISTER FOR SCHOOL.

00:32.332 --> 00:33.200
CUSTODY?!

00:33.233 --> 00:34.301
SHE WENT TO JAIL
FOR ME.

00:34.334 --> 00:35.969
NOW SHE'S OUT,
SO I'M GOING TO FIND HER.

00:36.003 --> 00:37.137
WHERE'S SILAS?

00:37.171 --> 00:38.639
HE HAD STUFF HE HAD TO DO.

00:38.672 --> 00:40.107
YEAH, STILL MAD AT ME.

00:40.140 --> 00:42.042
Silas:
WHAT'S INSIDE THE RADIO?

00:42.075 --> 00:44.578
YOU WOULDN'T HIDE IT IF IT
WAS JUST A RADIO. I KNOW YOU.

00:44.611 --> 00:46.947
YOU WANT THAT WEED TO BE HERE
WHEN YOU COME BACK?

00:46.980 --> 00:49.149
I CAN'T BRING IT BACK
TO THE HALFWAY HOUSE WITH ME.

00:49.183 --> 00:50.517
HALF OF THAT STASH
IS NOW MINE.

00:50.551 --> 00:53.120
I'LL CUT YOU IN ON THE PROFIT.
I'LL BE FAIR.

00:53.153 --> 00:55.255
DOUG‐INATOR! [ LAUGHS ]

00:55.289 --> 00:59.126
LISTEN, WE NEED YOU ‐‐ ON
THE FIELD AND IN THE BOARDROOM.

00:59.159 --> 01:00.894
COME ON.
TELL ME YOU'RE IN.

01:00.928 --> 01:03.096
SILAS "GUN‐NERD."

01:03.130 --> 01:04.164
IT'S "GUN‐NARD."

01:04.198 --> 01:06.166
HI.
I'M MAXEEN, THE ARTIST.

01:06.200 --> 01:08.035
YOU'RE ‐‐
YOU'RE AMAZING.

01:08.068 --> 01:10.470
I WANT TO FEED YOU
AND PROBE YOUR HIGHER SELF.

01:10.504 --> 01:11.371
ARE YOU HUNGRY?

01:11.405 --> 01:14.007
I'M GONNA...
GET MY HIGHER SELF PROBED.

01:14.041 --> 01:15.309
YOU KNOW HOW IT IS.

01:21.815 --> 01:24.017
[ BEEPING ]

01:32.092 --> 01:34.061
WHAT THE SHIT
DO YOU WANT?

01:34.094 --> 01:36.430
IS YOUR MOMMY HOME,
EITHER OF YOU?

01:36.463 --> 01:37.364
IT'S IMPORTANT.

01:37.397 --> 01:39.967
<i>I'M SORRY. SHE'S OUT.</i>
<i>SORRY.</i>

01:40.000 --> 01:42.703
OKAY. CAN YOU TELL HER
I CAN SEE HER SHADOW?

01:42.736 --> 01:44.705
<i>SHE'S STILL OUT.</i>

01:44.738 --> 01:46.373
WELL, GREAT.

01:46.406 --> 01:50.010
WOULD YOU RELAY TO YOUR MOTHER
WHEN SHE GETS BACK

01:50.043 --> 01:52.746
THAT I RECEIVED THE PAPERS
SHE SENT

01:52.779 --> 01:56.216
AND I WOULD REALLY APPRECIATE ‐‐
REALLY APPRECIATE ‐‐

01:56.250 --> 02:00.053
THE OPPORTUNITY TO SEE AND SPEAK
WITH MY SON?

02:00.087 --> 02:03.123
<i>HE'S NOT HERE.</i>
<i>HE'S AT...</i>

02:03.156 --> 02:04.825
<i>SOCCER PRACTICE.</i>

02:04.858 --> 02:07.160
<i>MOM TOLD US</i>
<i>WHY YOU WENT TO JAIL ‐‐</i>

02:07.194 --> 02:08.729
<i>FOR KILLING A MEXICAN,</i>

02:08.762 --> 02:10.397
<i>A DEFENSELESS</i>
<i>WOMAN MEXICAN</i>

02:10.430 --> 02:12.599
<i>WHO DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE YOU KILLED HER.</i>

02:12.633 --> 02:15.736
<i>DID IT FEEL GOOD AT ALL,</i>
<i>THE KILLING?</i>

02:15.769 --> 02:18.071
<i>LIKE, MAKE THE PAIN</i>
<i>GO AWAY?</i>

02:18.105 --> 02:21.008
<i>I HAVE PAIN INSIDE ME.</i>
<i>AND DARKNESS.</i>

02:21.041 --> 02:23.777
<i>AND THERE'S A VOICE</i>
<i>INSIDE THE DARKNESS.</i>

02:23.810 --> 02:27.114
OKAY, OKAY. OKAY, JILL, CAN
WE COME OUT AND BE ADULTS NOW?

02:27.147 --> 02:29.016
[ BELL DINGS, OBJECT CLATTERS ]

02:29.049 --> 02:32.452
HEY! THAT'S MY METRONOME
WHEN I PLAY MY SPOONS.

02:32.486 --> 02:34.488
PLEASE. PLEASE!

02:34.521 --> 02:37.224
SHE SAYS STEVIE GOT THE LAST
SLOT AT THE WALDORF SCHOOL.

02:37.257 --> 02:40.594
<i>THE DEPOSIT IS...</i>
<i>$2,800.</i>

02:40.627 --> 02:43.830
<i>AND THE DEADLINE IS FRIDAY,</i>
<i>SO YOU SHOULD SEND A CHECK.</i>

02:43.864 --> 02:45.632
CERTIFIED, BIATCH.

02:48.168 --> 02:51.371
[ EERIE PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

02:59.546 --> 03:01.281
[ MUTTERS ]

03:03.083 --> 03:05.452
MM.
HI.

03:05.485 --> 03:09.556
UM, WHY IS YOUR APARTMENT WEIRD
AND FULL OF DANGER?

03:09.590 --> 03:11.825
'CAUSE COMFORT
IS THE FIRST SIGN OF DEATH.

03:11.859 --> 03:14.528
THIS PLACE KEEPS YOU
ON GUARD,

03:14.561 --> 03:19.600
JUMP‐STARTS YOUR BLOOD FLOW,
INCREASES OVERALL LIFE‐SPAN.

03:19.633 --> 03:21.869
I GOT A GRANT TO BUILD IT.

03:21.902 --> 03:23.737
[ CHUCKLES ]
OH, YEAH.

03:23.770 --> 03:26.507
IT'S AMAZING WHAT ONE MISSES
WHEN CROCKED ON MARGARI‐‐

03:26.540 --> 03:28.942
OH, HEY! OH!

03:28.976 --> 03:30.077
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:30.110 --> 03:31.979
I'M LOOKING
FOR THE OTHER ONE OF THESE.

03:32.012 --> 03:35.349
AH, SOMEONE'S HERE IN THE ROOM,
RIGHT HERE WITH US.

03:35.382 --> 03:38.318
RED SOCK.
LOOKS LIKE THIS ONE.

03:38.352 --> 03:40.153
DID YOU CHECK
THE HAMPER?

03:40.187 --> 03:41.688
YES,
I CHECKED THE HAMPER.

03:41.722 --> 03:43.390
OH!

03:43.423 --> 03:44.491
I'M THE HUSBAND.

03:44.525 --> 03:45.926
OH! HUSBAND.

03:45.959 --> 03:47.427
OH. [ CHUCKLES ]
EXCUSE ME.

03:47.461 --> 03:50.230
UH, THAT'S COOL, MAN.
I KNOW THE DRILL.

03:50.264 --> 03:52.299
I'LL COME BACK
FOR MY PANTS.

03:52.332 --> 03:53.333
UH...

03:56.003 --> 03:58.038
WHERE'S
THE FUCKIN' DOORKNOB?

03:58.071 --> 04:00.340
RELAX.
WE'RE POLYAMOROUS.

04:02.309 --> 04:04.011
OH.

04:04.044 --> 04:05.779
WELL, WHERE DID YOU SLEEP
LAST NIGHT?

04:05.812 --> 04:07.181
IN THE MIDDLE.

04:07.214 --> 04:08.916
OF US?

04:08.949 --> 04:12.119
YOU GUYS FUCK.
I'LL MAKE EGGS.

04:23.463 --> 04:26.200
THOSE ARE
THE CUSTODY PAPERS.

04:26.233 --> 04:28.235
YOU'RE PRO BONO, RIGHT?

04:29.937 --> 04:32.072
I'M SORRY.
DID YOU SAY SOMETHING?

04:32.105 --> 04:33.340
YOU'RE PRO BONO.

04:33.373 --> 04:34.274
OH, RIGHT.

04:34.308 --> 04:36.743
NO. BASICALLY,
I MADE A KILLING IN THE '90s

04:36.777 --> 04:38.278
OFF OF THOSE
BREAST IMPLANTS

04:38.312 --> 04:40.948
THAT GAVE ALL THOSE WOMEN
THYROID DISEASE.

04:40.981 --> 04:43.050
SO I LEFT
THE CORPORATE WORLD,

04:43.083 --> 04:44.718
AND THEN I GUESS
THIS IS ME GIVING BACK.

04:44.751 --> 04:47.187
OH.
IF I TAKE YOUR CASE.

04:47.221 --> 04:48.121
"IF"?

04:48.155 --> 04:50.023
WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE

04:50.057 --> 04:52.159
THE STEWARD HAVENS
TRAPPER KEEPER OF BROKEN DREAMS?

04:52.192 --> 04:55.395
I‐I REALLY THINK I WOULD.

04:55.429 --> 04:59.066
BASICALLY, MY CLIENTS
TELL ME THEIR STORIES

04:59.099 --> 05:02.069
FROM INSIDE THE CLINK,
AND ‐‐ AND I PUT THE BEST ONES

05:02.102 --> 05:05.038
IN THE STEWARD HAVENS
TRAPPER KEEPER OF BROKEN DREAMS.

05:05.072 --> 05:09.810
I READ THEM
WHEN I'M SAD OR HORNY...

05:09.843 --> 05:11.144
OR BOTH.

05:11.178 --> 05:12.446
MAYBE THAT'S WEIRD.

05:12.479 --> 05:15.115
BUT YOU SHOULD BE FOCUSING
ON TELLING ME SOMETHING

05:15.148 --> 05:18.118
WORTHY OF INDUCTION
INTO THESE GOLDEN PAGES.

05:18.151 --> 05:21.021
I CAN ONLY BALANCE THREE CLIENTS
AT ONE TIME.

05:21.054 --> 05:22.956
AND RIGHT NOW,
THERE'S ONE SLOT OPEN.

05:22.990 --> 05:25.125
THAT MEANS YOU'RE COMPETING
AGAINST A WOMAN

05:25.158 --> 05:26.994
WHO MADE HERSELF QUEEN
OF CELL BLOCK "D"

05:27.027 --> 05:28.228
BY CONTRACTING TB

05:28.262 --> 05:31.164
AND SNEEZING HER WAY
UP THE FOOD CHAIN

05:31.198 --> 05:32.533
AND AN ECUADORIAN

05:32.566 --> 05:36.303
WHO TURNED A PIGEON
INTO A WORKING TIME BOMB.

05:37.538 --> 05:40.040
[ IMITATES EXPLOSION ]

05:42.176 --> 05:46.346
M‐MY CELL MATE USED TO MAKE,
UH, FERMENTED YAM WINE

05:46.380 --> 05:47.281
IN OUR TOILET.

05:47.314 --> 05:52.352
THE FEATHERS.
THERE WERE SO MANY FEATHERS.

05:55.055 --> 05:58.892
THE MOB HAD MY MEXICAN HUSBAND
KILLED IN PRISON.

05:58.926 --> 06:00.127
GO ON.

06:00.160 --> 06:03.497
THEY MADE IT LOOK
LIKE A HATE CRIME.

06:03.530 --> 06:04.798
THE ARYANS.

06:04.831 --> 06:07.100
HIRED TO STAB HIM.

06:07.134 --> 06:12.005
THEY, UH, RIPPED HIS EYES OUT
WITH A BROKEN DOMINO TILE,

06:12.039 --> 06:15.008
AND WHEN THEY WERE FINISHED,
THEY BROUGHT ME

06:15.042 --> 06:19.580
[Voice breaking]
A BOX WITH HIS, UH...

06:21.181 --> 06:24.218
WITH WHAT?
W‐WHAT WAS IN THE BOX?

06:26.053 --> 06:27.454
I'M GONNA NEED, UM...

06:27.487 --> 06:30.390
ATTORNEY‐CLIENT PRIVILEGE
IN ORDER TO CONTINUE.

06:36.563 --> 06:40.200
LOOK, UH, EVEN WITH MY HELP,
YOU'RE FUCKED.

06:40.234 --> 06:43.904
YOUR SISTER IS THE ONLY MOM
YOUR KID KNOWS.

06:43.937 --> 06:46.874
YOU CAN SEND ALL THE LETTERS
YOU WANT, BUT, TRUST ME,
THEY'VE BEEN SHREDDED.

06:46.907 --> 06:48.475
AND BABIES CAN'T READ.

06:48.509 --> 06:51.778
SO WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO SHOW
A JUDGE THAT YOU'RE TRYING.

06:51.812 --> 06:53.113
HAS SHE ASKED YOU
FOR ANYTHING?

06:53.146 --> 06:56.817
[ Normal voice ] A STUPID
PRESCHOOL DEPOSIT ‐‐ $2,800.

06:56.850 --> 07:00.053
DO YOU HAVE
THAT KIND OF MONEY?
NO.
I‐I‐I CAN GET IT.

07:00.087 --> 07:03.223
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS.

07:03.257 --> 07:04.258
I DO.

07:04.291 --> 07:05.292
OKAY, UM...

07:05.325 --> 07:06.393
I DON'T.

07:06.426 --> 07:08.195
I DO.

07:08.228 --> 07:09.863
NEVER ACTUALLY TELL ME.

07:09.897 --> 07:11.999
WOULD I HAVE TO SEND IT,
YOU KNOW?

07:12.032 --> 07:14.067
WOULD I HAVE TO LOOK
AT HER SHIT‐EATING GRIN AND ‐‐

07:14.101 --> 07:16.270
NO, I'LL SEND IT.
THAT'S WHAT I'M HERE FOR.

07:16.303 --> 07:19.106
ACTUALLY, I'D LIKE YOU
TO FOCUS IN ON GETTING A JOB.

07:19.139 --> 07:20.941
RIGHT.
A REAL JOB,

07:20.974 --> 07:24.411
GIVEN THE TERRIFICALLY UNCLEAR
NATURE OF YOUR INCOME.

07:24.444 --> 07:25.646
NOW...

07:25.679 --> 07:30.217
PLEASE TELL ME WHAT
THE ARYANS PUT INTO THAT BOX.

07:31.418 --> 07:33.987
THAT'S ALL THAT
I'VE BEEN THINKING OF.

07:34.988 --> 07:37.024
NEXT TIME.

07:41.895 --> 07:44.164
Silas: WHAT'S WITH
ALL THE NEW SHIT?

07:44.198 --> 07:47.601
WHAT?
I BOUGHT A FEW THINGS.

07:47.634 --> 07:49.303
AND YOU FINANCED THIS
HOW?

07:49.336 --> 07:50.938
UH, MULTIPLE
STUDENT LOANS.

07:50.971 --> 07:52.606
YOU'RE APPLYING TO SCHOOL?

07:52.639 --> 07:54.975
THERE'S THIS "THANK ME
FOR GOING TO PRISON FOR YOU

07:55.008 --> 07:57.144
BY GOING TO COLLEGE"
KIND OF REQUEST ON THE TABLE,

07:57.177 --> 07:58.946
BUT I DON'T THINK
I'M ACTUALLY GONNA GO.

07:58.979 --> 08:01.315
GOOD FOR YOU.
YOU DON'T NEED TO THANK HER.

08:01.348 --> 08:03.450
REALLY? 'CAUSE I'M FEELING
KIND OF GUILTY.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.886
I SAY YOU SCAM THAT MONEY.
ENJOY IT.

08:05.919 --> 08:08.555
GET YOURSELF A HOT TUB.
VESPA.

08:08.589 --> 08:11.391
ZERO GUILT. OKAY?

08:11.425 --> 08:12.726
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

08:12.759 --> 08:15.195
NANCY WANTS TO SEE ME.
CAN I COME?

08:15.229 --> 08:16.563
IT'S A BUSINESS MEETING.

08:16.597 --> 08:17.998
DRUG BUSINESS.

08:18.031 --> 08:19.366
IT'S WHAT OUR FAMILY DOES,
SHANE.

08:19.399 --> 08:22.870
ONLY NOW
WE'RE EQUAL PARTNERS.

08:22.903 --> 08:24.004
SINCE WHEN?

08:24.037 --> 08:25.072
SINCE LAST NIGHT.

08:25.105 --> 08:26.540
WE HAVE A NEW RELATIONSHIP,

08:26.573 --> 08:28.642
WHERE SHE TREATS US
LIKE REAL PEOPLE,

08:28.675 --> 08:31.612
WHERE WE DON'T HAVE TO LISTEN
TO EVERYTHING SHE SAYS

08:31.645 --> 08:33.547
OR BLINDLY FOLLOW ORDERS.

08:33.580 --> 08:37.017
SO, WHEN NANCY TELLS US TO GO
TO COLLEGE, WHAT DO WE DO?

08:37.050 --> 08:38.819
WE BUY HOT TUBS?

08:38.852 --> 08:41.889
FREE AT LAST, MY BROTHER.

08:41.922 --> 08:44.191
FREE AT LAST!

08:55.602 --> 09:00.507
SO, I WAS THINKING, IF
WE'RE GONNA BE A PARTNERSHIP ‐‐

09:00.541 --> 09:02.109
I NEED YOU TO DEAL.

09:02.142 --> 09:03.310
THAT IS NOT A PARTNERSHIP.

09:03.343 --> 09:05.879
THAT IS A "YOU TELLING ME
WHAT TO DO"‐SHIP.

09:05.913 --> 09:08.048
I'M NOT GONNA DEAL.
WE'LL HIRE DEALERS.

09:08.081 --> 09:09.383
THERE'S NO TIME.

09:09.416 --> 09:12.052
HOW MUCH WOULD WE GET IF YOU
CASHED IN WHAT WE HAVE NOW?

09:12.085 --> 09:15.189
IN THIS TOWN, WITH THAT QUALITY,
10 GRAND, EASY.

09:15.222 --> 09:17.524
IF I WERE DEALING,
WHICH I'M NOT,

09:17.558 --> 09:20.093
'CAUSE I'M NOT YOUR ERRAND
BOY ‐‐ I'M A BUSINESSMAN.

09:20.127 --> 09:22.229
BUT IF YOU
WERE GOING TO SELL IT.

09:23.964 --> 09:26.400
SILAS,
WE HAVE TO START SOMEWHERE.

09:26.433 --> 09:30.037
HELLO? I'M INCARCERATED.
WHEN CAN YOU SELL IT?

09:30.070 --> 09:32.639
TOMORROW, IF I TRY...

09:32.673 --> 09:35.042
AND YOU SAY, "PLEASE."

09:35.075 --> 09:36.443
SO, YOU'LL DO IT.

09:36.476 --> 09:39.079
FROM THAT SPECIAL CHINESE PLACE
WAY OUT IN BROOKLYN.

09:39.112 --> 09:41.048
I WOULD GIVE YOU THE NAME,
BUT LIKE YOU SAID,

09:41.081 --> 09:42.182
YOU'RE INCARCERATED,

09:42.216 --> 09:44.017
SO YOU'D PROBABLY
NEVER HAVE TIME TO GO.

09:44.051 --> 09:47.254
LET'S SEE ‐‐
CRUNCHY NOODLES IN DUCK SAUCE,

09:47.287 --> 09:48.755
FRIED RICE.

09:48.789 --> 09:52.726
WISH I'D HAVE GOTTEN ENOUGH
FOR BOTH OF US, BUT I DIDN'T.

09:52.759 --> 09:55.329
YOU SEEM HOSTILE.

09:55.362 --> 09:56.930
OH, DO I?

09:56.964 --> 09:58.165
I JUST ‐‐ I THOUGHT

09:58.198 --> 10:00.367
WE WERE GONNA FINISH OUR TALK
FROM LAST NIGHT.

10:00.400 --> 10:04.404
MAYBE APOLOGIZE
FOR OUR SINS FROM THE PAST.

10:04.438 --> 10:06.673
AND I DIDN'T REALIZE
YOUR IDEA

10:06.707 --> 10:08.475
OF A BUSINESS MEETING
WAS ASKING ‐‐

10:08.509 --> 10:10.677
IS ‐‐ IS THERE
A HORSE ON FIRE BEHIND ME?

10:10.711 --> 10:14.281
THIS GUY ‐‐ I THINK HE'S
A DEALER, BUT I'M NOT SURE.

10:14.314 --> 10:17.050
LOOK.
DON'T BE OBVIOUS.

10:18.819 --> 10:21.321
FREEZE! D. E. A.!

10:22.222 --> 10:24.057
DID HE TURN AROUND?
SEE?

10:24.091 --> 10:26.059
WE CAN BE A GREAT TEAM.

10:26.093 --> 10:28.362
[ HORN HONKS ]

10:28.395 --> 10:29.396
[ SIGHS ]

10:29.429 --> 10:31.198
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

10:31.231 --> 10:33.400
I HAVE A JOB INTERVIEW.

10:36.970 --> 10:38.739
SILAS, PLEASE.

10:44.444 --> 10:45.946
YES. FINE.

10:45.979 --> 10:50.284
THE STASH WILL BE CASH
BY TOMORROW.

10:50.317 --> 10:52.853
UM...

10:52.886 --> 10:56.089
I DIDN'T HAVE TIME
TO GET LUNCH.

10:56.123 --> 10:58.926
THAT CRISPY‐DUCK THING
SOUNDED SO GOOD.

10:58.959 --> 11:01.161
YOU CAN GET MORE, RIGHT?

11:03.830 --> 11:07.201
AW. THANK YOU, SWEETIE.

11:08.735 --> 11:11.004
WHAT? HERE?

11:11.038 --> 11:13.340
AH, NO CAN DO, NANCE.

11:13.373 --> 11:16.143
IF I DON'T HAVE A JOB,
I CAN'T GET MY KID BACK.

11:16.176 --> 11:17.945
DO YOU REALLY WANT
ANOTHER KID?

11:17.978 --> 11:20.147
LOOK, SOFTBALL SEASON
STARTS IN A WEEK.

11:20.180 --> 11:22.015
I'M GUESSING THAT'S THE ONLY
REASON THEY HIRED ME HERE.

11:22.049 --> 11:23.450
I CAN'T ASK
FOR AN ASSISTANT NOW.

11:23.483 --> 11:24.985
[ SIGHS ]

11:25.018 --> 11:27.321
I GOT STEROIDS.

11:27.354 --> 11:28.488
WOW. RAD.

11:28.522 --> 11:30.190
HELP ME.

11:30.224 --> 11:32.659
MAYBE I COULD SLIP A FEW BUCKS
UNDER THE TABLE.

11:32.693 --> 11:33.861
YOU COME IN TWICE A WEEK.

11:33.894 --> 11:35.762
NO, I NEED TO BE
IN THE SYSTEM ‐‐

11:35.796 --> 11:38.198
PAY STUBS, W‐9s,
DOCUMENTATION.

11:38.232 --> 11:41.101
I'M SORRY, LADY.
[ GLASS CLUNKS, SHATTERS ]

11:41.134 --> 11:43.303
[ SIGHS ]
DOUG...

11:43.337 --> 11:44.638
DOUG...

11:44.671 --> 11:46.473
DOUG. DOUG!

11:46.507 --> 11:48.809
I KNOW YOU'RE NOT
THE SMARTEST, QUICKEST,

11:48.842 --> 11:50.077
MOST EMPATHETIC PERSON,

11:50.110 --> 11:52.012
BUT IT'S NO SECRET

11:52.045 --> 11:53.614
THAT FOR MUCH
OF OUR RELATIONSHIP,

11:53.647 --> 11:56.149
YOU'VE BEEN AN IRON BALL
ATTACHED TO MY ANKLE.

11:56.183 --> 11:57.885
I'VE ‐‐ I'VE CARRIED YOU
AROUND

11:57.918 --> 12:00.087
FOR A CONSIDERABLE AMOUNT
OF TIME.

12:00.120 --> 12:02.189
MY LEG'S TIRED NOW.

12:02.222 --> 12:04.958
SO, IF WHAT
YOU'RE OFFERING ME NOW,

12:04.992 --> 12:08.128
IN THIS, MY MOST DESPERATE
MOMENT, IS REJECTION,

12:08.161 --> 12:10.731
I MIGHT JUST FREAK OUT HERE
IN YOUR OFFICE

12:10.764 --> 12:13.066
WITH YOUR NICE NEW WINDOWS,
FURNITURE...
OKAY, OKAY.
NANCE. NANCY.

12:13.100 --> 12:14.535
NANCE.
...LARGE PICTURE OF YOU.

12:14.568 --> 12:16.203
NANCY.
TCHOTCHKES. NO.

12:16.236 --> 12:17.037
OW.

12:17.070 --> 12:18.205
HEY, HEY, HEY.

12:18.238 --> 12:21.175
YOU'RE THE CLOSEST THING
I HAVE TO FAMILY.

12:23.043 --> 12:26.146
I LOVE YOU,
NANCY BOTWIN.

12:26.180 --> 12:29.082
LOOK, TAKE SOME PETTY CASH,
GO TO BLOOMIES,

12:29.116 --> 12:31.351
GET YOURSELF A NICE DRESS,
SOME SHOES.

12:31.385 --> 12:34.521
YOU START TOMORROW, LEGIT.
DOES THAT SOUND GOOD?

12:34.555 --> 12:36.657
OKAY.

12:36.690 --> 12:37.958
DON'T BE LATE.

12:37.991 --> 12:39.226
I WON'T.
GOOD.

12:39.259 --> 12:41.395
NOW STAB ME IN THE ASS.

12:46.800 --> 12:51.605
THERE'S THIS VIDEO ONLINE
OF MAXEEN PUTTING A POPSICLE

12:51.638 --> 12:54.141
[ MAXEEN MOANS]
UP HER LADY HOLE
FROM ONE OF HER SHOWS.

12:54.174 --> 12:55.909
WILL YOU HELP ME
WITH THIS SHEET?

12:55.943 --> 12:57.678
THEY INVITED ME OVER TOMORROW.
DO I GO?

12:57.711 --> 13:01.148
WHY AM I HESITATING?
SO WHAT IF SHE HAS A HUSBAND?

13:01.181 --> 13:03.383
[ MAXEEN MOANS]
I CAN DO FREAKY.
AM I GETTING OLD?

13:03.417 --> 13:06.353
DID I DIE IN COPENHAGEN?
I DID.

13:06.386 --> 13:08.589
I COULDN'T SPEAK THE LANGUAGE.
I DIED.

13:08.622 --> 13:09.656
HAND ME THOSE PILLOWS.

13:09.690 --> 13:12.092
LAST NIGHT, I DREAMED I ATE
A SHORT, HAIRY HOT DOG.

13:12.125 --> 13:13.327
DOES THAT MEAN
I TOUCHED HIM?

13:13.360 --> 13:14.995
NO, THAT MEANS
YOU BLEW HIM.

13:15.028 --> 13:17.097
POPSICLE REPRESENTS
THE EPHEMERAL PENIS.

13:17.130 --> 13:21.301
ITS MELTING AFFIRMS
THE STRENGTH OF WOMAN.

13:21.335 --> 13:24.104
I GET IT.
THAT'S BEAUTIFUL.

13:24.137 --> 13:25.839
SHE SOUNDS CRAZY.

13:25.873 --> 13:28.909
[ CHUCKLES ]
I KNOW. RIGHT?

13:28.942 --> 13:30.410
UH, WAS THAT PILLOWCASE
EGYPTIAN COTTON?

13:30.444 --> 13:32.079
EGYPTIAN COTTON
IS SO COMFORTABLE.

13:32.112 --> 13:35.215
COMFORTABLE. MAYBE I'M ‐‐
I'M TOO COMFORTABLE.

13:35.249 --> 13:38.418
YOUR NEW BEDROOM
LOOKS EXPENSIVE.

13:38.452 --> 13:41.488
