16:13.707 --> 16:16.009
YEAH, WELL, YOU AND
EVERYBODY ELSE IN THIS CITY.

16:16.043 --> 16:19.246
BUT TRUST ME...
THIS STUFF IS GOLD.

16:19.279 --> 16:23.016
THAT'S THE THING, MAN.
IT'S ABOUT TRUST, OKAY?

16:23.050 --> 16:25.185
I DON'T KNOW YOU.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'RE ABOUT.

16:25.219 --> 16:28.522
THAT COULD BE SHIT
THAT MAKES ME FUCKING FATTER.

16:28.555 --> 16:29.723
OKAY.

16:29.756 --> 16:31.358
HOW ABOUT A FREE SAMPLE?

16:34.928 --> 16:37.264
WHY WOULD YOU GIVE ME
FREE POT?

16:37.297 --> 16:40.100
'CAUSE IF YOU LIKE IT,
YOU GIVE ME A CALL
AND BUY SOME MORE.

16:40.133 --> 16:43.937
WE DEVELOP TRUST.
NO STRINGS.

16:43.971 --> 16:48.275
HERE'S MY NUMBER.
PUT IT IN YOUR PHONE.

16:48.308 --> 16:50.177
THANKS.

16:50.210 --> 16:54.047
HEY.
COULD I GET SOME OF THAT?

16:59.920 --> 17:02.222
Klein: HAVE DINNER
WITH ME TONIGHT?

17:05.092 --> 17:06.927
ARE YOU TALKING TO ME?

17:06.960 --> 17:10.330
I AM DEFINITELY TALKING
TO YOU.

17:10.364 --> 17:11.865
OH. UH...

17:11.899 --> 17:14.234
[ BEEPS ]
FLATTERED.

17:15.402 --> 17:17.704
WHAT'S THE C. E. O. DOING
IN THE COPY ROOM?

17:17.738 --> 17:19.439
NOT MAKING COPIES.

17:19.473 --> 17:21.175
NO, HE'S NOT.

17:21.208 --> 17:21.975
SO...

17:22.009 --> 17:25.078
NOBU, 8:00.

17:25.112 --> 17:27.748
I‐I WOULD LIKE
TO KEEP MY JOB.

17:27.781 --> 17:29.049
WELL, YOU'RE ALLOWED
TO SAY NO.

17:29.082 --> 17:33.153
I'M NOT SAYING NO.
I'M SAYING...

17:33.187 --> 17:34.688
WHAT AM I SAYING?

17:34.721 --> 17:36.056
YOU'RE SAYING, "FUCK OFF."

17:36.089 --> 17:39.760
UH, NO. AM I?
YEAH.

17:39.793 --> 17:42.963
I DON'T THINK SO.
DEFINITELY NOT.

17:42.996 --> 17:46.099
I'M SAYING NOT TONIGHT...
OR THIS WEEK.

17:46.133 --> 17:48.135
LIKE YOUR SHOES.

17:48.168 --> 17:51.004
THANKS. YOU BOUGHT 'EM
FOR ME ‐‐ PETTY CASH.

17:51.038 --> 17:53.140
OH. SORRY.

17:53.173 --> 17:55.042
THAT'S COMING OUT
OF YOUR PAYCHECK.

17:55.075 --> 17:58.045
RIGHT, RIGHT.

17:58.078 --> 17:59.713
WHAT YOU GOT THERE?

17:59.746 --> 18:01.048
OH, STUFF.

18:01.081 --> 18:02.850
MARKET RESEARCH.

18:02.883 --> 18:05.452
GOT TO STAY AHEAD
OF THE COMPETITION.

18:05.485 --> 18:07.688
UH‐HUH.

18:07.721 --> 18:09.590
DOUG, WHAT TIME IS IT?

18:09.623 --> 18:12.426
5 INCHES.
AND 5:00. WHY?

18:12.459 --> 18:14.094
OOPS.

18:14.127 --> 18:17.164
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

18:17.197 --> 18:18.765
Man: WHAT THE HELL?

18:18.799 --> 18:20.968
♪♪ WOW WOW WOW ♪♪

18:21.001 --> 18:23.537
♪♪ FUNK, FUNK, FUNK,
FUNK, FUNK ♪♪

18:23.570 --> 18:26.306
YOU GUYS HAVE BEEN MARRIED
A WHILE, HUH?

18:26.340 --> 18:27.307
16 YEARS.

18:27.341 --> 18:29.409
CHARLES WAS
MY ENGLISH PROFESSOR.

18:29.443 --> 18:30.611
THAT'S ADORABLE.

18:30.644 --> 18:31.545
AND THIS PLACE,

18:31.578 --> 18:33.313
THIS AMAZING,
LIFE‐EXTENDING APARTMENT ‐‐

18:33.347 --> 18:35.082
HOW IS THAT WORKING
FOR YOU, CHARLES?

18:35.115 --> 18:36.283
I LOVE IT.
GREAT. YEAH.

18:36.316 --> 18:39.620
'CAUSE YOU'RE LIKE 85 OR 90,
RIGHT?

18:39.653 --> 18:41.955
I'M LOOKING
FOR PIGEON EGGS.

18:41.989 --> 18:43.590
OH. OF COURSE.

18:43.624 --> 18:46.126
UH, WHEN DO YOU GO AWAY?

18:46.159 --> 18:49.129
DOES OUR RELATIONSHIP
MAKE YOU UNCOMFORTABLE?

18:50.297 --> 18:52.933
I HAD A MOMENT OF PANIC
LAST NIGHT

18:52.966 --> 18:55.302
WHERE I SAID,
"AM I UNCOMFORTABLE ABOUT THIS?

18:55.335 --> 18:57.304
"AND IF SO,
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

18:57.337 --> 18:58.805
"PERHAPS I NEED
TO LOOK INWARD

18:58.839 --> 19:00.974
AND ASK THE BIG
BLAH‐DI‐BLAH QUESTIONS."

19:01.008 --> 19:02.976
SO I DID THAT
FOR FIVE MINUTES,

19:03.010 --> 19:06.847
AND, LONG STORY SHORT,
THAT'S NOT THE CASE.

19:06.880 --> 19:09.716
I'M JUST FREAKED OUT BY YOU
SPECIFICALLY.

19:09.750 --> 19:12.553
ANDY ‐‐
AND, OBVIOUSLY,
YOU'RE NOT MY SEXUAL RIVAL,

19:12.586 --> 19:15.956
WHAT WITH YOUR PENIS BEING
A SOFT VOID FILLED WITH SONNETS,

19:15.989 --> 19:17.991
WHILE MINE IS FULL
OF PROUD SMURFS

19:18.025 --> 19:20.227
BANGING TINY BLUE HAMMERS
AGAINST MY BALLS.

19:20.260 --> 19:21.862
ANDY ‐‐
AND LAST NIGHT,

19:21.895 --> 19:23.864
THERE WAS A DREAM
ABOUT A HOT DOG.

19:23.897 --> 19:25.699
DID I, UH ‐‐
DID I SUCK YOU OFF?

19:25.732 --> 19:27.067
ANDY...
WHAT'S UP?

19:27.100 --> 19:28.635
I HAVE CANCER.

19:28.669 --> 19:31.205
WHAT?

19:31.238 --> 19:33.473
THE BUMPY FLOORS,
THE LIFE‐EXTENDING APARTMENT,

19:33.507 --> 19:37.978
THE DANGER ROOM ‐‐
SHE BUILT THAT FOR ME.

19:38.011 --> 19:41.648
OH. OHHHH.

19:41.682 --> 19:44.484
I'M WITH YOU, PAL.

19:44.518 --> 19:46.286
IT'S IN MY PANCREAS.

19:46.320 --> 19:48.222
WOW. YOU'RE NOT OLD.
YOU'RE JUST DYING.

19:48.255 --> 19:49.823
I'M AN ASSHOLE.
YOU WERE RIGHT.

19:49.857 --> 19:51.258
I'M NOT YOUR RIVAL.

19:51.291 --> 19:53.160
IT'S NOT A COMPETITION.

19:53.193 --> 19:57.531
WE'RE POLYAMOROUS
BECAUSE SHE'S...

19:57.564 --> 19:59.199
SHE'S AMAZING.

20:00.200 --> 20:03.470
AND, UM,
IT'S WHAT SHE WANTS.

20:03.504 --> 20:07.007
AND I DON'T WANT TO
LEAVE HER ALONE.

20:07.040 --> 20:11.311
SHE'S TRYING TO SAVE YOU,
AND YOU'RE TRYING TO SAVE HER.

20:13.080 --> 20:15.182
CAN YOU WORK WITH THAT?

20:21.388 --> 20:22.756
[ MOANS ]

20:22.789 --> 20:24.892
♪♪ DRINK IT DOWN ♪♪

20:24.925 --> 20:26.860
♪♪ NICE AND SLOW ♪♪

20:26.894 --> 20:29.162
♪♪ IT MAKES YOU FEEL GOOD ♪♪

20:29.196 --> 20:30.964
♪♪ REAL GOOD ♪♪
[ MOANING ]

20:30.998 --> 20:32.966
♪♪ MAKE YOUR MOVE ♪♪

20:33.000 --> 20:35.002
♪♪ FEEL THE GROOVE ♪♪

20:35.035 --> 20:39.106
♪♪ YOU KNOW YOU LOOK GOOD ♪♪

20:39.139 --> 20:41.141
♪♪ FIZZY YUM YUM YUM YUM YUM ♪♪

20:41.175 --> 20:42.809
♪♪ FIZZY YUM YUM ♪♪

20:42.843 --> 20:46.013
♪♪ FIZZY YUM YUM YUM YUM YUM ♪♪

20:46.046 --> 20:47.681
♪♪ FIZZY YUM YUM ♪♪
[ GASPING ]

20:47.714 --> 20:50.984
♪♪ FIZZY YUM YUM YUM YUM YUM ♪♪

20:51.018 --> 20:52.719
♪♪ FIZZY YUM YUM ♪♪

20:52.753 --> 20:55.355
OH, I WAS LOOKING
FOR THAT.

20:59.159 --> 21:01.228
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

21:02.629 --> 21:05.499
OH. COPY ROOM.

21:05.532 --> 21:07.100
NANCY.

21:07.134 --> 21:08.936
ABOUT EARLIER...

21:08.969 --> 21:11.738
OH, INAPPROPRIATE
BUT HARMLESS.

21:11.772 --> 21:14.508
NO, NO, NO, NO.
I WAS WRONG.
SERIOUSLY,
DO YOU WANT THE SHOES BACK?

21:14.541 --> 21:15.509
'CAUSE I FEEL TERRIBLE.

21:15.542 --> 21:17.945
I NEVER WOULD HAVE ASKED YOU OUT
IF I'D KNOWN

21:17.978 --> 21:21.515
YOU WERE ONE OF THESE
CRAZY, UPTIGHT, MILITANT,
ANTIDRUG BITCHES.

21:21.548 --> 21:25.285
THAT'S JUST
A LITTLE INTENSE FOR ME.

21:25.319 --> 21:27.621
AND YOU SHOULDN'T BE
ABUSING THE XEROX

21:27.654 --> 21:29.356
FOR YOUR
PERSONAL AGENDA.

21:29.389 --> 21:31.124
OH.

21:31.158 --> 21:34.628
UM, I DIDN'T ‐‐ I'M NOT ‐‐
I LOVE SUSHI.

21:34.661 --> 21:37.231
NOBU.
8:00, DID YOU SAY?

21:37.264 --> 21:39.466
'CAUSE I‐I
CAN MAKE THAT HAPPEN.

21:39.499 --> 21:41.134
I GOT TO RUN.

21:41.168 --> 21:43.370
KEEP THE SHOES.

21:49.710 --> 21:51.378
[ DOOR OPENS ]

21:53.514 --> 21:54.815
WHERE'S YOUR BROTHER?

21:54.848 --> 21:56.583
I MADE YOU SOMETHING.

21:56.617 --> 22:00.087
MM. LAST TIME YOU SAID THAT,
I GOT A MACARONI NECKLACE.

22:00.120 --> 22:03.390
UM, NO ‐‐
UH, A TERRORIST VIDEO.

22:03.423 --> 22:05.726
I FIGURED WHEN YOU'RE
OUT OF THE HALFWAY HOUSE,

22:05.759 --> 22:07.160
YOU'LL NEED A PLACE TO CRASH,

22:07.194 --> 22:09.630
SO I TRIED TO REMEMBER WHAT THE
AGRESTIC BEDROOM LOOKED LIKE.

22:11.999 --> 22:14.168
WAS I CLOSE?

22:15.702 --> 22:19.806
IT'S, UH...WOW.

22:19.840 --> 22:21.275
WHERE DID YOU ‐‐

22:21.308 --> 22:23.977
I COULDN'T REMEMBER IF YOUR BED
WAS A KING OR A QUEEN.

22:24.011 --> 22:25.245
IT WAS A QUEEN.

22:25.279 --> 22:27.481
OH, CRAP.
ARE YOU SURE?

22:27.514 --> 22:31.084
WHERE DID YOU GET THE MONEY
TO ‐‐ TO PAY FOR ALL THIS?

22:31.118 --> 22:33.020
AND AS I ASK THAT ‐‐

22:33.053 --> 22:35.389
I APPLIED FOR A LOAN,
SOME LOANS, FOR COLLEGE.

22:35.422 --> 22:38.725
YOU CAN'T ‐‐

22:38.759 --> 22:40.594
ALL THIS HAS TO GO BACK.

22:40.627 --> 22:45.532
THAT MONEY WAS SUPPOSED TO GO
TOWARDS SCHOOL, LIKE I SAID.

22:45.566 --> 22:47.768
SO, YOU DON'T LIKE IT?

22:47.801 --> 22:49.069
OH, GOD.
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

22:49.102 --> 22:51.638
I WAS TRYING TO SAY
THANK YOU.
FOR WHAT?

22:51.672 --> 22:52.739
HEY.

22:52.773 --> 22:54.208
THE AGRESTIC BEDROOM.

22:54.241 --> 22:56.510
AND HOW RICH DO YOU THINK
WE USED TO BE?

22:56.543 --> 22:58.979
WE GOT ALL THAT STUFF
AT ‐‐ AT J. C. PENNEY.

22:59.012 --> 23:00.480
YOU PUT THIS TOGETHER?

23:00.514 --> 23:04.585
YOU WERE RIGHT.
I SHOULD HAVE BOUGHT A VESPA.

23:10.257 --> 23:16.263
TODAY, I OPENED UP
31 BROAD STREET, DOWNTOWN.

23:16.296 --> 23:18.332
THE WHOLE BUILDING?
YEAH.

23:18.365 --> 23:20.601
POSSIBLY THE BLOCK
SURROUNDING IT.

23:20.634 --> 23:24.071
MAYBE PARTS OF STATEN ISLAND,
IF THE WINDS ARE FAVORABLE.

23:24.104 --> 23:27.140
THERE'S ‐‐ THERE'S GONNA BE
A LOT OF DEMAND.

23:27.174 --> 23:29.076
I NEED YOU TO COME BY
TOMORROW.

23:29.109 --> 23:31.245
BRING EVERYTHING
YOU HAVE LEFT.

23:31.278 --> 23:32.846
I DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING LEFT.

23:32.880 --> 23:34.381
REALLY?

23:34.414 --> 23:37.084
YEAH.
I'M OUT.

23:37.117 --> 23:39.019
OH, YOU HAVE YOUR MOTHER'S
WORK ETHIC.

23:39.052 --> 23:40.153
CAN I HAVE THE CASH?

23:40.187 --> 23:42.789
WELL, THERE IS
NO CASH YET.

23:42.823 --> 23:44.992
FROM SELLING THE DRUGS.

23:45.025 --> 23:47.094
THERE'S NO CASH
FROM SELLING THE DRUGS.

23:47.127 --> 23:49.830
THERE'S ALWAYS CASH
FROM SELLING THE DRUGS.

23:49.863 --> 23:51.231
THAT'S WHY WE SELL DRUGS.

23:51.265 --> 23:54.101
NOT WHEN YOU GIVE THEM AWAY
FOR FREE.

23:54.134 --> 23:58.105
WHY WOULD WE...

23:58.138 --> 23:59.573
OH, YOU DIDN'T.

23:59.606 --> 24:01.074
IT'S CALLED A LOSS LEADER.

24:01.108 --> 24:04.011
YOU SELL A PRODUCT
AT A LOSS TO INCREASE
FUTURE SALES.

24:04.044 --> 24:05.412
IT'S GOOD BUSINESS.

24:05.445 --> 24:06.980
I NEED MONEY NOW!

24:07.014 --> 24:09.616
NOT THE PROMISE OF MONEY ‐‐
ACTUAL MONEY.

24:09.650 --> 24:12.619
I OWE YOUR AUNT
A‐A PRESCHOOL PAYMENT BY FRIDAY.

24:12.653 --> 24:14.454
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]
IF I CAN'T PROVIDE THAT,

24:14.488 --> 24:18.692
I AM DOUBLE‐DIPPED
IN THREE SHADES OF F‐F‐F‐FUCK!

24:18.725 --> 24:20.227
YOUR CELLPHONE IS RINGING!

24:20.260 --> 24:22.696
I KNOW.
[ SIGHS ]

24:22.729 --> 24:26.033
42 NEW VOICE MAILS.

24:26.066 --> 24:27.267
42 NEW CLIENTS.

24:27.301 --> 24:30.404
I GOT ORDERS ON HERE
FOR TWICE WHAT WE LET GO.

24:30.437 --> 24:32.806
I AM BETTER AT THIS
THAN YOU KNOW.

24:32.840 --> 24:33.807
[ SIGHS ]

24:33.841 --> 24:35.242
WE'RE GONNA NEED
MORE SUPPLY ‐‐

24:35.275 --> 24:37.110
A LOT MORE.

24:37.144 --> 24:40.080
THIS SUPPLY
THAT YOU SPEAK OF ‐‐

24:40.113 --> 24:42.115
CAN'T EXACTLY PUT IT
ON A MasterCard.

24:42.149 --> 24:43.817
DID YOU THINK
ABOUT THAT?

24:43.851 --> 24:47.221
WELL, UH...
WHAT SHOULD WE DO?

24:50.324 --> 24:52.793
SHANE!
SHANE!

24:52.826 --> 24:54.661
YEAH?

24:54.695 --> 24:57.097
HOW MUCH, UM, CASH
DO YOU HAVE?

24:57.130 --> 24:58.932
I DON'T KNOW.
LIKE A GRAND.

24:58.966 --> 25:01.168
YEAH.
COULD YOU GO GET IT, PLEASE?

25:01.201 --> 25:02.402
WHY?

25:02.436 --> 25:04.238
'CAUSE I NEED IT.

25:04.271 --> 25:05.839
WE NEED IT.

25:05.873 --> 25:07.374
[ SIGHS ]

25:07.407 --> 25:10.043
I DON'T WANT YOU TO GO
BACK TO PRISON.

25:10.077 --> 25:12.346
IT'S MY FAULT
YOU WENT THERE ONCE.

25:15.015 --> 25:18.151
SWEETIE,
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH,

25:18.185 --> 25:20.020
AND THIS ROOM ‐‐
I‐I DO LIKE THIS ROOM.

25:20.053 --> 25:21.922
I'D BE HONORED
TO SLEEP HERE ‐‐

25:21.955 --> 25:24.291
I WANT IT BACK,
PLUS 20%.

25:26.159 --> 25:27.928
WHAT ABOUT
YOUR LOAN CHECKS?

25:27.961 --> 25:29.229
I ONLY GOT ONE SO FAR,

25:29.263 --> 25:32.332
AND YOU SAID THOSE
ARE FOR SCHOOL AND HOT TUBS.

25:32.366 --> 25:34.535
I KNOW WHAT I SAID.
THANK YOU, SWEETIE.

25:34.568 --> 25:36.069
THANKS, BUDDY.

25:36.103 --> 25:38.505
YEAH, WHATEVER.

25:38.539 --> 25:41.508
[ MAN SINGING IN PASHTU ]

25:41.542 --> 25:44.778
[ VEHICLE PASSES ]

25:44.811 --> 25:47.080
[ CONVERSATION IN PASHTU ]

25:58.025 --> 25:59.693
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:17.611 --> 26:19.613
[ EXPLOSION ]

26:21.448 --> 26:24.184
SO, THERE'S BEEN A GLITCH
IN THE SUPPLY CHAIN.

26:24.218 --> 26:25.953
WHAT'S THAT MEAN,
A GLITCH?

26:25.986 --> 26:27.955
I'M NOT SAYING
I CAN'T GET YOU WEED. I CAN.

26:27.988 --> 26:29.690
BUT IT'S GONNA BE
AT LEAST ANOTHER MONTH.

26:29.723 --> 26:33.060
I DON'T HAVE ANOTHER MONTH.
IS THERE SOMEONE YOU CAN CALL?

26:33.093 --> 26:35.762
IT'S FUCKIN' AFGHANISTAN.
WHO DO YOU WANT ME TO CALL?

26:35.796 --> 26:39.132
THEN G‐GIVE ME YOUR WEED.

26:39.166 --> 26:41.134
NO, THESE ARE
MY LAST THREE JOINTS.

26:41.168 --> 26:44.972
HOW MUCH DO YOU WANT
FOR THEM?

26:45.005 --> 26:47.574
GOT TO GIVE IT A MONTH.

26:51.078 --> 26:53.113
COME ON, BABY.

26:54.948 --> 26:56.149
[ SIGHS ]

26:56.183 --> 26:58.986
[ <i>CRYING</i>]
Shayla:
<i>THAT'S STEVIE CRYING</i>

26:59.019 --> 27:01.288
'CAUSE MOM TOLD HIM
HE COULDN'T' GO TO WALDORF NOW

27:01.321 --> 27:04.024
Taylor:
BECAUSE THE DEPOSIT MONEY
YOUR CREEPY LAWYER PROMISED

27:04.057 --> 27:05.826
<i>NEVER SHOWED UP.</i>

27:05.859 --> 27:09.062
AND SINCE THAT'S THE SCHOOL
ALL HIS FRIENDS ARE GOING TO,

27:09.096 --> 27:10.964
<i>HE WON'T BE ABLE TO PLAY</i>
<i>WITH THEM.</i>

27:10.998 --> 27:12.599
<i>I'M SURE</i>
<i>HE'LL GET OVER IT.</i>

27:12.633 --> 27:15.636
I NEVER HAD ANY FRIENDS,
AND I TURNED OUT FINE.

27:15.669 --> 27:17.337
[ SPOONS CLICKING ]

27:17.371 --> 27:19.806
MAYBE YOUR MOTHER
COULD PAY FOR IT.

27:19.840 --> 27:21.141
<i>OH, SHE WILL.</i>

27:21.175 --> 27:24.111
SHE JUST WANTED YOU TO SEE
THE DISAPPOINTMENT YOU CAUSED

27:24.144 --> 27:25.812
<i>BEFORE SHE MADE IT</i>
<i>ALL BETTER.</i>

27:25.846 --> 27:28.382
<i>IT'S OKAY, STEVIE.</i>
<i>DON'T CRY.</i>

27:29.917 --> 27:32.052
<i>JENNY'S GOING.</i>

27:32.085 --> 27:34.454
<i>BRENDAN'S GOING.</i>

27:34.488 --> 27:36.757
<i>VICTORIA'S GOING.</i>

27:36.790 --> 27:38.725
<i>MARK IS GOING.</i>

27:38.759 --> 27:40.127
<i>AMY'S GOING.</i>

27:40.160 --> 27:43.063
